The Symbol of Mandorla, meaning simply “Almond” can be found in Western religious, alchemical & esoteric texts. It is also known as Vesica Piscis, a mathematical shape created by the intersection of two disks of the same radius. Because of the nature of their intersection, the center of each disk is found at the perimeter of the other.

The almond can symbolise the containment or hiding of something sacred or valuable in a hard shell. Similarly, for the medievals, the almond was the symbol of embryo in uterus. Christ or Mary were often portrayed in such iconography. 

Because of the above mentioned, many later researchers, esotericists & occultists compare Mandorla to the Yoni (Womb/Vulva), the gateway of all births, container of Consciousness & all forms commonly found in Indian spiritual traditions.
